\chapter{Serving Static Websites}

This article has been inspired by a simple [question](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/6084360/node-js-as-a-simple-web-server?rq=1) at stackoverflow. How to use node as a simple webserver.

As always there are many ways to skin the cat. The best and more reliable method would be to use the [express serve-static server](https://github.com/expressjs/serve-static).


\begin{verbatim}
var finalhandler = require('finalhandler')
var http = require('http')
var serveStatic = require('serve-static')

// Serve up public/ftp folder
var serve = serveStatic('public/', {'index': ['index.html', 'index.htm']})

// Create server
var server = http.createServer(function(req, res){
  var done = finalhandler(req, res)
  serve(req, res, done)
})


// Listen
server.listen(3000)
\end{verbatim}